In [176]:
import matplotlib.cm as cm

grey = np.zeros(shape=np.shape(body))


# mask off lower values to just get locations of cells
# mask value subject to change
body_masked = np.ma.masked_where(body<1000, body)
nucleus_masked = np.ma.masked_where(nucleus<1000, nucleus)

# increase the intensity of the remaining values for better contrast
body_masked = body_masked*1000
nucleus_masked = nucleus_masked*1000

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.imshow(grey, cmap=cm.gray)
ax.imshow(body_masked, cmap='Blues')
ax.imshow(nucleus_masked, cmap="Reds")

plt.show()

import re # REEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEE

def load_images(directory):
    # Loading filenames from directory
    list_files = os.listdir(directory)
    # remove the hidden file from the list
    list_files.pop(0)
    regex = re.compile(r'^(W\d{4}F\d{4}T\d{4}Z\d{3}C[1|3])\.tif$') # dont question it removed
    filtered = [i for i in list_files if regex.match(i)]
    dic = {}
    for c1, c3 in zip(filtered[0::2], filtered[1::2]):
        wf = c1[0:10]
        dic[wf] = (c1, c3)
    
    return dic


temp = load_images('images/projection')

def make_images(dic):
    
    for wf in dic:
        nucleus = io.imread('images/projection/'+dic[wf][0], plugin="tifffile")
        body = io.imread('images/projection/'+dic[wf][1], plugin="tifffile")
        grey = np.zeros(shape=np.shape(body)) # background
        
        # mask off lower values to just get locations of cells
        # mask value subject to change
        body_masked = np.ma.masked_where(body<1000, body)
        nucleus_masked = np.ma.masked_where(nucleus<1000, nucleus)

        # increase the intensity of the remaining values for better contrast
        body_masked = body_masked*1000
        nucleus_masked = nucleus_masked*1000

        fig, ax = plt.subplots()
        ax.imshow(grey, cmap=cm.gray)
        ax.imshow(body_masked, cmap='Blues')
        ax.imshow(nucleus_masked, cmap="Reds")

        plt.savefig('output/'+wf+'.png')
